ANALYSIS.TITLE: TCGA/ICGC PanCancer Specimen-Level Alignment for Specimen HX16L from Participant HX16
ANALYSIS.DESCRIPTION: Specimen-level BAM from the reference alignment of specimen HX16L from donor HX16. This uses the SeqWare BWA-MEM PanCancer Workflow version 2.6.5 available at https://s3.amazonaws.com/oicr.workflow.bundles/released-bundles/Workflow_Bundle_BWA_2.6.5_SeqWare_1.1.0-alpha.5.zip. This workflow can be created from source, see https://github.com/ICGC-TCGA-PanCancer/Seqware-BWA-Workflow/tree/2.6.5. For a complete change log see https://github.com/Seqware-BWA-Workflow/Seqware-BWA-Workfow/blob/2.6.5/CHANGELOG.md. Input BAMs are prepared and submitted to GNOS server according to the submission SOP documented at: https://wiki.oicr.on.ca/display/PANCANCER/PCAP+%28a.k.a.+PAWG%29+Sequence+Submission+SOP+-+v1.0. Please note the reference is hs37d, see ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/technical/reference/phase2_reference_assembly_sequence/README_human_reference_20110707 for more information. Briefly this is the integrated reference sequence from the GRCh37 primary assembly (chromosomal plus unlocalized and unplaced contigs), the rCRS mitochondrial sequence (AC:NC_012920), Human herpesvirus 4 type 1 (AC:NC_007605) and the concatenated decoy sequences (hs37d5cs.fa.gz).

CUSTOM.DESCRIPTION: GRCh37 (hs37d5). See ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/technical/reference/phase2_reference_assembly_sequence/README_human_reference_20110707 for more information.
